\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 11.} In the premises, Li had to comply with the statutory duties under the F&IUO, F&IUR, CSSR, OS&HO and OS&HR to ensure the safety and health of the plaintiff.\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 12.} Since Li had the care and control of the site, he was also the occupier of the site within the meaning of the Occupiers Liability Ordinance Cap. 314 ("OLO"). He thus owed Chan the "common duty of care" under section 3 of OLO.\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 13.} Furthermore, there was an expressed or alternatively implied term of the contract of employment made between Chan and Li that Li had to provide Chan with a safe place and system of work at all times.\par}

\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li0\ri0\fi0\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 {\f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 14.} In a nutshell, Li owed Chan the following duties: - {\par}{\pard \fi-360 \li720 \ls8 
\qj \hyphpar0 \cbpat0 {\sa60\sb60\li720\ri0\fi-360\sl288\slmult1 \f10 \fs20 \cf1 \b0 \i0 \strike0 \ul0 (a) To provide and maintain a safe place of work for Chan;\par}
}

{\pard \fi-360 \li720 \ls9 
